  "prompt": "If members of the NITK IT batch 2016 were Game of Thrones, characters, who would be whom?",
  "response": "Drawing parallels between members of the NITK IT batch of 2016 and *Game of Thrones* characters would require knowing the personalities, roles, and dynamics of the batch members. However, here\u2019s a fun and generalized take on how such a comparison might play out:\n\n1. **Tyrion Lannister** \u2013 The witty, smart, and resourceful classmate who\u2019s always the life of the party and has a sharp sense of humor. They\u2019re the go-to person for advice or a clever comeback.\n\n2. **Jon Snow** \u2013 The noble and dependable leader who\u2019s always ready to step up. They might be a bit brooding but are universally respected for their integrity.\n\n3. **Daenerys Targaryen** \u2013 The ambitious and driven classmate with big dreams and a commanding presence. They\u2019re the one who\u2019s always pushing boundaries and inspiring others.\n\n4. **Arya Stark** \u2013 The fiercely independent and adventurous member of the batch. They\u2019re resourceful, clever, and unafraid to take risks.\n\n5. **Sansa Stark** \u2013 The graceful and diplomatic one who\u2019s great at handling tricky situations and keeping the peace. They\u2019ve grown into a strong and poised individual over the years.\n\n6. **Cersei Lannister** \u2013 The classmate with a strong personality who\u2019s not afraid to go after what they want. They\u2019re strategic and ambitious but can be polarizing.\n\n7. **Jaime Lannister** \u2013 The confident and skilled one who\u2019s a bit of a wildcard. They might have a complex personality but are ultimately loyal to their close friends.\n\n8. **Bran Stark** \u2013 The quiet, introspective one who\u2019s always observing and analyzing. They\u2019re wise beyond their years and often have profound insights.\n\n9. **The Hound (Sandor Clegane)** \u2013 The tough and rugged classmate who might seem intimidating but has a soft side. They\u2019re fiercely protective of their close friends.\n\n10. **Samwell Tarly** \u2013 The kind-hearted and studious one who\u2019s always ready to help. They\u2019re a bit unassuming but are incredibly intelligent and dependable.\n\n11. **Petyr Baelish (Littlefinger)** \u2013 The mastermind who\u2019s always thinking ahead and playing the long game. They\u2019re strategic and ambitious but sometimes a bit too cunning.\n\n12. **Brienne of Tarth** \u2013 The fiercely loyal and principled classmate who\u2019s always standing up for what\u2019s right. They\u2019re a natural leader and protector.\n\n13. **Joffrey Baratheon** \u2013 The classmate who\u2019s a bit difficult to deal with at times. They might have a strong personality but can be polarizing or challenging.\n\n14. **Theon Greyjoy** \u2013 The classmate who\u2019s gone through a journey of self-discovery and growth. They might have had their ups and downs but ultimately find their way.\n\n15. **Varys** \u2013 The quiet but observant classmate who knows everything that\u2019s going on. They\u2019re great at networking and keeping tabs on the batch\u2019s dynamics.\n\n16. **Robb Stark** \u2013 The natural leader who\u2019s respected by everyone. They\u2019re strong, determined, and always put the group\u2019s needs first.\n\nThis comparison is purely speculative and meant for fun! If you have specific traits or personalities in mind for the batch members, feel free to share, and I can refine the analogy further!",
